      "body": "> mesosalpinx muscularus\r\n\r\nI suspect that this structure might be referring to the [myosalpinx](https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/agricultural-and-biological-sciences/mesosalpinx#:~:text=Myosalpinx,al.%2C%202015).), or tunica muscularis. If it is the case, it is a separate layer than the mesosalpinx, and therefore it wouldn't need a term for antimesosalpinx muscularis. I don't think that the mesosalpinx have a muscular layer.",
