      "body": "@aleixpuigb from fallopian tube experts for ontology placement: \r\nBegin forwarded message:\r\n\r\nFrom: \"Nordgren, C. Erik\" <nordgren@sas.upenn.edu>\r\nSubject: Re: Fallopian tube cell type ontology\r\nDate: November 26, 2024 at 10:11:13 AM EST\r\nTo: \"Quardokus, Ellen M\" <ellenmq@iu.edu>, Aleix Puig <aleix@ebi.ac.uk>\r\nCc: \"Fisher, Stephen A\" <safisher@sas.upenn.edu>, Kate O'Neill <Kathleen.O'neill2@pennmedicine.upenn.edu>, \"Kuang, Da\" <kuangda@seas.upenn.edu>\r\n\r\nHi Ellen & Aleix,\r\n\r\nHaving consulted further with Kate, I wanted to get back to you with more specificity on the placement of the new functional tissue unit ontological terms we need added for Fallopian tube.\r\n\r\nSo, under \"muscle layer of oviduct\", should be placed:\r\nmesosalpinx muscularus\r\nantimesosalpinx muscularus\r\n\r\nAnd under \"mucosa of fallopian tube\", should be placed:\r\nmesosalpinx epithelium\r\nantimesosalpinx epithelium\r\nAll of these terms would of course apply to both the left and right organs.\r\nDoes that give you what you need, in order to have these new terms added and published?\r\nErik\r\n",
